# ===================================================================
# Vault .gitignore — text-only backup, exclude bulk binary/raw content
# Generated 2026-04-28 by Claude (task-008 c1, approved in approvals.md)
# ===================================================================

# === macOS junk ===
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Icon?
._*

# === Bulk content (excluded from git, kept on Google Drive only) ===
# raw/ = 300MB original source materials (PDFs, course materials)
# attachments/ = 99MB rendered images
# These re-derive from raw/ via ingest pipeline; not worth versioning
MyBrain/raw/
MyBrain/attachments/
MyBrain/archive/

# === Obsidian workspace state (per-machine, not shared content) ===
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/cache
.obsidian/graph.json

# Plugins binaries (re-installable from community plugins)
.obsidian/plugins/*/main.js
.obsidian/plugins/*/styles.css
.obsidian/plugins/*/data.json

# === Claudian / daemon state (machine-specific, secrets-adjacent) ===
.claudian/

# === Clippings (web clipper raw output, often noisy) ===
Clippings/

# === Temp / system files ===
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.tmp/
.cache/

# === Logs (can be large, regenerable) ===
MyBrain/automation/logs/
MyBrain/automation/runs/

# === Approvals — keep tracked (it's the source of truth for AI ↔ user) ===
# (no exclude — approvals.md SHOULD be in git)

# === Career — KEEP TRACKED ===
# (resume / cover letters / applications.md are critical, all .md tracked)

# === Inbox — keep tracked (transient but small text) ===
# (no exclude — inbox/ stays in git)
